<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING COMPRESSOR AND CLUTCH, TWO CYLINDER RECIPROCATING TYPE - After 01/01/1993 (R-134a) - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - CLUTCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601704" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>CLUTCH</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clutch center bolt and washer using the spanner wrench to hold the clutch
                    pulley (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601703">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601703" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601703" filename="../figg16/G1601703.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Remove Clutch Center Bolt</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a clutch remover bolt into the clutch. Using the spanner wrench to hold the
                    clutch pulley in place, tighten the clutch bolt until the clutch pulley assembly is forced free from
                    the compressor output shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601704">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601704" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601704" filename="../figg16/G1601704.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Install Clutch Remover Bolt</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clutch field coil mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601705">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601705" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601705" filename="../figg16/G1601705.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Remove Coil Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clutch field coil from the compressor.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="hl1601705">
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that a key is properly inserted in the shaft of the compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount and center the field coil bracket. Tighten the four clutch field coil mounting
                    bolts to 13 to 17 ft-lbs. (18 to 23 N&#183;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601706">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601706" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601706" filename="../figg16/G1601706.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6. Tighten Coil Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Only use bolts that have a Loctite patch on the threads.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place clutch pulley assembly over the shaft, making sure to align the key way over the
                    shaft key (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601707">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601707" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601707" filename="../figg16/G1601707.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Clutch Pulley Assembly Over Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the clutch center bolt and washer to 20 to 25 ft-lbs. (27.1 to 33.9
                    N&#183;m) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601708">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601708" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601708" filename="../figg16/G1601708.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Tighten Clutch Center Bolt</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Spin the clutch pulley to verify there is no interference. Verify the clutch engages
                    when the proper voltage is applied.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
